{
  "stem": "10587.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 31.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was a-- it was on the main square of the town, but inside the complex there was a little square.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That-- because the building was like a-- a quadrangle building with apartments on the second floor.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Two-story building.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And-- and stores on the first floor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So we used to-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It wasn't too far from the temple, so we used to walk every Friday night, Saturday morning, and during high holidays or-- to the temple.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My grandfather used to wear a top hat.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And-- and everyone-- he purposefully walk-- walked diagonally through the main square, so that everyone would bow and-- and hold their hat and say, Good Shabbat, Mr.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Enoch.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Good Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he was well-known in the community, and was also a big man, and-- and quite a showman.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So-- In the temple, they used to sit on the western wall, only he and his son, which lived in the same building.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And-- and the son-in-laws, and-- like my father and other husbands from-- of my aunts.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It really was a very nice little Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "There was quite a few Jewish people that lived in Oswiecim.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And this-- unfortunately in 1941, this-- the community stopped to exist.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my brother and I used to be very close.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "My younger brother and I used to be very close.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And we would [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] horse around as much as we could, all day long.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But we did study quite hard as well, because we went to Polish school in the morning, to the cheder in afternoon, and my parents insisted that we do our homework.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "So we played hard and we also studied hard.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] When the war broke out, the-- the Germans occupied Poland in I believe September of 1939.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "They didn't have far to go to find Oswiecim because we were right very close to the German border.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And a few weeks later, they renamed the main square where I lived to Adolf Hitler's Platz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And the town was renamed back to Auschwitz, which at one time, I believe, must have been Auschwitz, the name of Auschwitz during the time when-- when Auschwitz was part of Austria.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were six siblings.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My oldest brother, his name is Herman.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my sister, Fela.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My brother Abraham, which is Romek.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Unfortunately, he was killed in the-- in the last few days of the-- just before the liberation, on a death march.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my sister Regina, my younger brother [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Sheik ?], his name was Joshua.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Sheik ?] was his Polish name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Or that's what they called him, mostly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so we were a large family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] miraculously, the four of us made it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The rest, my father, my mother, and my youngest brother was killed in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father's name was Isaac, [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yitzva ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother's name Rachel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother was mainly involved with the children and the household.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father was in the lumber business.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember as a little boy, my father used to cut lumber in the-- in the Carpath mountains in-- in Poland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they used to slide down the hills, the lumber, as they-- and every piece of lumber used to have a stamp which was stamped with a-- by a-- with a hammer, which was IB.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the lumber was then channeled into the lumber mill, and cut to various type of lumber, for construction, for paper pulp, for telephone and electric poles, as well as lumber that used to support the coal mines, special type of [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] sizes of lumber.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we used to play many times in the-- in the-- my brother and I used to play around railroad, because everything was shipped by railroad.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] but this was mainly in-- in the mountain areas.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So when we used to go there on vacation, or sometimes during the summer time, we would go there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Speaking of playing, what kind of toys did you play with?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Do you remember?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- we really didn't have too many toys, but we played soccer.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We played-- we used to make our own hockey sticks, and play hockey.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because there was really not too much traffic.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most traffic was pedestrian.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and-- or horses pulled wagons.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was very few cars in the city of Oswiecim as I remember it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm glad you ask this question because my mother-- my grandmother name was Rose.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And people used to tell me that she used to come around every holiday, like for-- for Passover, or Rosh Hashanah, Yom Kippur, and deliver food and-- and coals and-- to the-- to the poor people.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
